reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on February 3, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars I don't give many 5 star reviews- these are awesome for kids and adults!
reviews.reviewText: Picked up the smaller set as a last minute Xmas gift need and they are super awesome. We all play with them, but definitely need the larger set, if not two larger sets. Its SO fun to build with and you can make anything you can think of, so the possibilities are endless. They hold together really well and are really durable.One of the best toys our kids have. Ages 2 and 4 love them.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on February 1, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Keeps toddlers busy
reviews.reviewText: We love our magnatiles! We’ve tried many brands but these are our favorite - so durable and the magnets are very strong. My 2.5 year old is rough as can be with his toys but these bad boys keep up with him. Only problem is there’s not enough, we have two big boxes of them and he thinks we need more lol

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 14, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 4.0 out of 5 stars 4 stars because of false advertising
reviews.reviewText: The magnets are great, high quality and kids love them. Four stars is because of false advertising. The first photo in this add is WAY more than one box of these. For exampe it comes with only 4 of the tall pointy triangles and I counted 28 in the picture. The subsequent pics are more realistic. There aren't enough pieces included to make all the suggested ideas that are demonstrated in the book. We love them so we are ordering another set to be able to make more things.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 26, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Great customer service, Not great magnets or magnet placement
reviews.reviewText: Updated to add that customer service reached out to help make the issue right and was very helpful. Thus I change from 2 to 5 stars.I was so excited to find a set of magnetic tiles for a good price but was very disappointed when I found that they don't magnet together very well and the structures that you build are not very sturdy even if it's just a basic cube. I ordered them early for Christmas so it was past the window to return them by the time we opened them on Christmas. If you try to build a ramp structure the magnets are placed in such a way that there are big divets so it's not a smooth enough surface for the car to drive over.
